## What is a static method?

A **static method** is a method that can be called without creating an object of the class.

```
 public class Student {

  public static String school = "Neighborhood HS";

  public static String getSchool() {
    return school;
  }

  . . .
}
```

Static Methods
- Cannot access or change the values of instance variables 
- Can access or change the values of static variables 
- Do not have a `this`(#e7e8ea) reference 
- Cannot use the class's instance variables or call non-static methods

To call a **static method**, use the `ClassName`(#e7e8ea) and the dot operator.

```
System.out.println(Student.getSchool());
```
